# Live site only — do nothing locally

All runtime work happens on the **deployed Vercel app** (https://listing-optimizer-builder.vercel.app). This machine is for **edit → commit → push** only.

## Never do locally

- `npm run dev` or any local server to test ingest/optimize
- Crawls, scrapes, or live fetches (Firecrawl, Rainforest, Amazon PDPs)
- curl/scripts against `localhost` for real ASINs or URLs
- Writing API keys into tracked repo files (use Vercel env vars + gitignored `.env.local` if the user sets keys themselves)

## Do instead

1. **Commit and push** — Vercel deploys from GitHub automatically.
2. **Live smoke tests** — hit `https://listing-optimizer-builder.vercel.app` API routes or UI only when testing real behavior.
3. **Deterministic tests** — mocked fixtures in CI on GitHub (not on this computer); no live crawls in CI either unless explicitly against production with user approval.
4. **Secrets** — set in Vercel project environment variables, never committed.

When the user wants to test ingestion or optimization, direct them to the live dashboard or run checks against the production URL only.
